can help change that.

85
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:40,500
- [grunts] Yeah!
- [Greg] Ow!

86
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:41,583
[horn honks]

87
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:45,833
Who knows? You two might
surprise yourselves.

88
00:04:48,208 --> 00:04:49,333
[car door closes]

89
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:52,875
Don't forget to
unload the dishwasher!

90
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:54,541
[groans]

91
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:56,041
- Whoa!
- All right, Greg.

92
00:04:56,125 --> 00:04:57,805
We've got one hour to
get this place ready.

93
00:04:57,875 --> 00:04:59,125
Ready for what?

94
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:00,916
The party.

95
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:05,250
What? No way! Mom and Dad would
never let you have a party!

96
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:08,666
They'll never even know, and
it's not my party anyway.

97
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:10,750
It's our party.

98
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:13,250
Whoa. What do you
mean "our party"?

99
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:17,041
The Heffley brothers are
throwing this party together.

100
00:05:17,125 --> 00:05:18,833
The Heffley brothers?

101
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:23,916
That's right. You
and me, together.

102
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:27,875
