Rodrick's, like, an expert at this stuff.

181
00:09:43,125 --> 00:09:47,458
But it seems like he's just getting
us to do all the hard stuff.

182
00:09:47,541 --> 00:09:51,250
You don't get it, Rowley.
Rodrick's depending on me.

183
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:54,333
Our party's gonna be… epic.

184
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:59,375
[whistles]

185
00:10:05,791 --> 00:10:07,833
Um. [gulps]

186
00:10:15,166 --> 00:10:16,791
[gasps]

187
00:10:22,458 --> 00:10:23,791
Whoa.

188
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:27,791
- [cackles]
- [screams]

189
00:10:27,875 --> 00:10:29,208
[mike feedback]

190
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:32,666
I don't think we should
be in Rodrick's bedroom.

191
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:35,625
Relax, we're just in
here for the table.

192
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:40,976
[Rowley] Do you think
there will be party games,

193
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,375
like charades or pin
the tail on the donkey?

194
00:10:43,458 --> 00:10:45,333
- [amplifier sounds]
- [cymbals clatter]

195
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:47,708
It's not that kind
of thing, Rowley.

196
00:10:47,791 --> 00:10:50,791
High-school parties are totally
different than little-kid parties.

197
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:52,041
How do you know?

198
00:10:52,125 --> 00:10:54,291
I just know stuff.

199
00:10:54,375 --> 00:10:56,855
Listen, we're gonna be the only
middle schoolers at this thing.

200
00:10:56,916 --> 00:11:00,333
We've gotta blend in. Just
try and be cool, okay?

201
00:11:00,416 --> 00:11:03,458
But pin the tail on
the donkey is cool.

202
00:11:05,625 --> 00:11:06,625
Wait, what?

203
00:11:11,916 --> 00:11:15,625
"See you after the party."

204
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:17,583
Oh, no.

205
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:20,208
What's going on? Is it stuck?

206
00:11:20,291 --> 00:11:23,500
It's not stuck! I think
Rodrick locked the door.

207
00:11:23,583 --> 00:11:25,666
But why would he do that?

208
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:28,291
What about the party? What
about the Heffley brothers?

209
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:32,583
It was, uh, probably
just a joke.

210
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:36,875
[grunting] Rodrick? Rodrick!

211
00:11:37,666 --> 00:11:39,166
- [loud music playing]
- [knocking]

212
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:40,250
Rodrick!

213
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:41,875
- [pounding]
- [glass breaking]

214
00:11:42,458 --> 00:11:43,708
Rodrick!

215
00:11:43,791 --> 00:11:45,458
[increases music volume]

216
00:11:45,541 --> 00:11:46,625
Rodrick!

217
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:56,708
[teenagers cheering]

218
00:11:58,291 --> 00:12:00,541
[grunts]

219
00:12:00,625 --> 00:12:01,625
Rodrick!

220
00:12:02,416 --> 00:12:03,416
Is he coming?

221
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:04,625
Just wait here, okay?

222
00:12:07,041 --> 00:12:09,166
But I have tap-dancing
lessons in the morning.

223
00:12:09,250 --> 00:12:10,375
