00:26:54,333 --> 00:26:56,750
That seems like bad stuff.

495
00:26:56,833 --> 00:26:59,083
This information is
like gold, Rowley!

496
00:26:59,166 --> 00:27:01,291
It's what makes having an
older brother worth it.

497
00:27:03,375 --> 00:27:06,208
But why is Rodrick being so
nice to you all of a sudden?

498
00:27:08,375 --> 00:27:11,666
I don't know. Maybe 'cause he
just likes having me around.

499
00:27:11,750 --> 00:27:14,666
You know what? You wouldn't
understand. You're an only child.

500
00:27:14,750 --> 00:27:15,750
No offense.

501
00:27:16,416 --> 00:27:23,166
Well, I'm glad I'm an only child. 'Cause
this brother stuff is complicated.

502
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:31,000
["Requiem in D Minor
Lacrimosa" playing]

503
00:27:44,958 --> 00:27:45,958
[song stops]

504
00:27:50,541 --> 00:27:53,166
[continues playing drums]

505
00:27:53,833 --> 00:27:55,000
Rodrick!

506
00:27:57,291 --> 00:27:58,583
Rodrick!

507
00:28:00,041 --> 00:28:01,333
Rodrick!

508
00:28:05,125 --> 00:28:06,375
What?

509
00:28:06,458 --> 00:28:10,875
You need to teach me something new.
You never got past rule number one.

510
00:28:10,958 --> 00:28:14,250
You only get one rule a week.
That's Rodrick Rule number two.

511
00:28:14,333 --> 00:28:15,666
[rim shot]

512
00:28:15,750 --> 00:28:18,333
What? That's not fair.

513
00:28:18,416 --> 00:28:19,833
Life's not fair.

514
00:28:21,833 --> 00:28:24,583
Rule number three. And now you
made me break rule number two.

515
00:28:24,666 --> 00:28:26,458
[sighs] Fine.

516
00:28:28,041 --> 00:28:29,250
Ow! What the...

517
00:28:29,333 --> 00:28:31,250
I've been looking for that.

518
00:28:31,333 --> 00:28:32,333
What is this?

519
00:28:32,416 --> 00:28:34,458
It's an echo pedal. We need it…

520
00:28:34,541 --> 00:28:37,458
[echoes, singing]
…for the talent show.

521
00:28:37,541 --> 00:28:41,375
Oh, yeah, the talent
show. I'm trying out too.

522
00:28:41,458 --> 00:28:44,541
You? You don't have any talent.

523
00:28:45,833 --> 00:28:48,750
Yeah, I'm in Rowley's magic act.

524
00:28:48,833 --> 00:28:50,416
<i>I'm his…</i>

525
00:28:50,500 --> 00:28:51,583
<i>assistant.</i>

526
00:28:52,916 --> 00:28:54,875
[scoffs]

527
00:28:54,958 --> 00:28:59,041
[laughs] Man, they're... They're
gonna laugh you off the stage.

528
00:28:59,125 --> 00:29:02,125
Yeah, I know. Mom's making me.

529
00:29:03,041 --> 00:29:05,208
Hey, do you think you
can get me out of this?

530
00:29:05,291 --> 00:29:08,958
[laughs] Sorry, you c... You
can't leave your friends hanging.

531
00:29:09,041 --> 00:29:10,208
Rodrick Rule number four.

532
00:29:10,291 --> 00:29:14,125
All right, enough with the rules. How
about you teach me something for real?

533
00:29:14,208 --> 00:29:15,416
Like what?

534
00:29:15,500 --> 00:29:16,833
I don't know.

535
00:29:17,625 --> 00:29:21,666
Maybe you could teach me how
to play the drums or something.

536
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:27,375
[snickers] Are you sure you could
handle that, little brother?

537
00:29:28,416 --> 00:29:29,833
- Yeah!
- All right.

538
00:29:30,541 --> 00:29:31,541
It's simple.

539
00:29:31,625 --> 00:29:37,708
You just gotta grip the sticks,
feel the flow, and let it rip.

540
00:29:41,041 --> 00:29:46,708
Okay, now loosen up that wrist a bit.
Keep it flowing. Feel the rhythm.

541
00:29:46,791 --> 00:29:50,916
That... Th-That's it! [laughs]
You've got potential, little bro.

542
00:29:52,333 --> 00:29:53,333
- [door opens]
- [gasps]

543
00:29:53,416 --> 00:29:56,833
Are you ready to rock?

544
00:29:57,708 --> 00:30:00,333
[Greg narrating] <i>Bill Walter is
the lead singer of Löded Diper,</i>

545
00:30:00,416 --> 00:30:03,208
<i>even though he's something
like 35 years old.</i>

546
00:30:03,291 --> 00:30:05,375
<i>I'm pretty sure Rodrick
asked him to join</i>

547
00:30:05,458 --> 00:30:08,250
<i>because he got named "Most
Likely to Be a Rock Star"</i>

548
00:30:08,333 --> 00:30:10,416
<i>when he was in high school.</i>

549
00:30:10,500 --> 00:30:11,958
[laughs]

550
00:30:13,125 --> 00:30:15,708
Beat it, kid. Grown-ups
are talking here.

551
00:30:17,458 --> 00:30:21,208
Nah, that... That's all
right. He can stay. He's cool.

552
00:30:24,041 --> 00:30:25,708
Whatever you say, dude.

553
00:30:25,791 --> 00:30:27,875
You ready to burn
this place down?

554
00:30:27,958 --> 00:30:29,875
We are Löded Diper!

555
00:30:29,958 --> 00:30:31,416
One, two, three, four!

556
00:30:31,500 --> 00:30:33,500
[rock music playing]

557
00:30:34,083 --> 00:30:35,875
[Bill] ♪ <i>All right</i> ♪

558
00:30:35,958 --> 00:30:38,958
[screams]

559
00:30:39,041 --> 00:30:41,750
- [music continues]
- [groans]

560
00:30:41,833 --> 00:30:44,500
- ♪ <i>So, he sent us underground</i> ♪
- Huh?

561
00:30:44,583 --> 00:30:46,583
♪ <i>Oh, yeah</i> ♪

562
00:30:47,208 --> 00:30:48,666
♪ <i>You never listened</i> ♪

563
00:30:49,416 --> 00:30:52,166
[vocalizes]

564
00:30:52,250 --> 00:30:54,250
[babbling]

565
00:30:55,333 --> 00:30:58,166
Isn't setting the
table Greg's job?

566
00:30:58,250 --> 00:31:00,541
He's hanging out with his
brother in the basement.

567
00:31:01,041 --> 00:31:03,666
I didn't want to interrupt
their "together time."

568
00:31:03,750 --> 00:31:05,708
Listen, I... [stammers]

569
00:31:05,791 --> 00:31:09,458
Do you think it's a good idea that those
guys are spending so much time together?

570
00:31:09,541 --> 00:31:11,708
Why wouldn't it be a good idea?

571
00:31:13,833 --> 00:31:16,083
It's just that...
[stammers] Well, I mean...

572
00:31:16,166 --> 00:31:19,625
Look, who knows what kind of
stuff Rodrick is teaching Greg?

573
00:31:19,708 --> 00:31:21,958
- [music stops]
- [Rodrick] Somebody farted!

574
00:31:22,041 --> 00:31:23,416
- [all coughing]
- [Greg groans]

575
00:31:23,500 --> 00:31:24,750
Ew, gross.

576
00:31:24,833 --> 00:31:26,208
[all laughing]

577
00:31:27,833 --> 00:31:30,416
- [echoes] Somebody farted!
- [all laughing]

578
00:31:32,750 --> 00:31:34,333
I rest my case.

579
00:31:34,416 --> 00:31:36,708
The boys are bonding, Frank.

580
00:31:36,791 --> 00:31:38,958
Isn't that what
we want to happen?

581
00:31:39,666 --> 00:31:44,125
Look, sometimes my older brother,
Joe, would string me along,

582
00:31:44,208 --> 00:31:45,750
and then I'd get burned.

583
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:48,041
Greg needs to protect himself.

584
00:31:48,125 --> 00:31:51,791
Because if Rodrick pulls the rug out
from under him, he's gonna get hurt.

585
00:31:51,875 --> 00:31:55,625
We can't police every interaction
between these boys, Frank.

586
00:31:56,208 --> 00:31:57,888
They need to work
things out on their own.

587
00:31:57,958 --> 00:32:01,416
[sighs] Maybe you're
right. But I just... I...

588
00:32:01,500 --> 00:32:04,666
Now why don't you just take off that
tie, and try and relax a little?

589
00:32:05,666 --> 00:32:09,083
[clears throat] I'll, uh,
go get washed up for dinner.

590
00:32:09,166 --> 00:32:11,166
[music resumes]

591
00:32:15,041 --> 00:32:16,791
[handle jiggles]

592
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:21,583
Hey! Didn't this
door used to lock?

593
00:32:24,125 --> 00:32:25,250
So, you guys are telling us

594
00:32:25,333 --> 00:32:29,458
that you have no idea why the
bathroom door suddenly doesn't lock?

595
00:32:29,541 --> 00:32:33,375
Wait. We have a
bathroom on this floor?

596
00:32:33,458 --> 00:32:38,458
[sighs] I feel like there's
something the boys aren't telling us.

597
00:32:39,041 --> 00:32:41,833
Greg, would you like
to say something?

598
00:32:43,625 --> 00:32:44,625
Um…

599
00:32:47,583 --> 00:32:51,333
Actually, something did
happen on Friday night.

600
00:32:51,916 --> 00:32:53,583
Something I should've
told you about.

601
00:32:56,958 --> 00:32:58,041
[groans]

602
00:32:58,833 --> 00:33:01,541
I went in the bathroom, and
I tried to lock the door.

603
00:33:01,625 --> 00:33:02,625
But I couldn't.

604
00:33:03,666 --> 00:33:07,500
I think I must have broken it by
shutting it too hard or something.

605
00:33:07,583 --> 00:33:08,583
Sorry.

606
00:33:13,666 --> 00:33:14,666
[sighs]

607
00:33:14,750 --> 00:33:18,375
Okay. Mystery solved.
Let's move on.

608
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:20,000
[whispers] Nice save.

609
00:33:20,666 --> 00:33:25,916
Boys, your father and I are taking another
shot at celebrating our anniversary

610
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:28,333
since our first
attempt got cut short.

611
00:33:28,416 --> 00:33:30,750
You're going away this weekend?

612
00:33:30,833 --> 00:33:32,666
Yes, but don't worry.

613
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:34,990
You see, we're not gonna leave
you two on your own again.

614
00:33:35,041 --> 00:33:36,416
Why? Who's coming over?

615
00:33:37,500 --> 00:33:40,625
You two boys are gonna
visit your grandpa.

616
00:33:40,708 --> 00:33:44,166
Wait. At Leisure Towers? But
there's nothing to do there.

617
00:33:44,250 --> 00:33:47,166
Oh, there's plenty to
do at Grandpa's complex.

618
00:33:47,250 --> 00:33:50,000
Shuffleboard, bingo, the pool.

619
00:33:50,083 --> 00:33:53,375
[singsongy] And you know how
much my dad loves board games!

620
00:33:54,250 --> 00:33:55,500
Board games?

621
00:33:55,583 --> 00:33:56,583
Come on, guys.

622
00:33:56,666 --> 00:34:00,000
You know Grandpa appreciates it
when you spend time with him.

623
00:34:00,083 --> 00:34:01,958
- But... [sighs]
- Mom's right, Greg.

624
00:34:02,041 --> 00:34:04,500
It's been way too long since
we paid Grandpa a visit.

625
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:07,708
This... This is gonna be great.

626
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:11,958
Okay, guys. Better get packed.

627
00:34:12,708 --> 00:34:14,291
Greg, I'll help you.

628
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,583
- Rodrick?
- Yeah?

629
00:34:16,666 --> 00:34:18,000
Good role modeling.

630
00:34:18,625 --> 00:34:20,750
Well, I try.

631
00:34:29,208 --> 00:34:30,916
Ready, set, go!

632
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,916
Whoo-hoo! Whee!

633
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,250
- [crashes]
- Aha!

634
00:34:35,833 --> 00:34:37,166
- [snores]
- [groans]

635
00:34:37,250 --> 00:34:39,541
- [elevator bell dings]
- Ooh. Hey!

636
00:34:39,625 --> 00:34:40,791
[squeaking]

637
00:34:40,875 --> 00:34:41,916
[elevator bell dings]

638
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,250
Dagnabbit!

639
00:34:44,416 --> 00:34:48,541
Okay, boys! This is Gutbusters!

640
00:34:48,625 --> 00:34:53,000
One player reads a card, and the
other players try not to laugh.

641
00:34:53,083 --> 00:34:54,208
Them's the rules!

642
00:34:54,291 --> 00:34:56,333
- That sounds so fun!
- [sighs]

643
00:34:56,416 --> 00:34:58,416
- Roll the dice, Grandpa!
- [dice rattling]

644
00:34:59,708 --> 00:35:01,875
[Grandpa] Ha! Snake eyes!

645
00:35:01,958 --> 00:35:03,208
It's your turn to read, Greg.

646
00:35:03,291 --> 00:35:09,458
[groans] "A man who would pun,
would just as easily pick a pocket."

647
00:35:10,583 --> 00:35:12,375
[both snickering]

648
00:35:15,541 --> 00:35:17,000
Huh? I don't get it.

649
00:35:17,583 --> 00:35:19,583
- [Rodrick laughs]
- [Grandpa laughs]

650
00:35:20,166 --> 00:35:21,458
Come on, Rodrick!

651
00:35:21,541 --> 00:35:23,208
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

652
00:35:23,291 --> 00:35:25,583
[laughing] I'm sorry, I...
I... I-I-I couldn't help it.

653
00:35:25,666 --> 00:35:27,708
[laughing] That one
gets me every time.

654
00:35:27,791 --> 00:35:29,791
[exhales] All right, boys.

655
00:35:29,875 --> 00:35:35,166
Now, why don't you clean up this
mess while I take a potty break?

656
00:35:35,250 --> 00:35:39,000
Okay, Grandpa. But don't
take too long in there.

657
00:35:40,875 --> 00:35:43,041
I can't believe you
agreed to coming here.

658
00:35:43,125 --> 00:35:45,333
Why didn't you at least
try to get us out of it?

659
00:35:45,416 --> 00:35:49,041
Can't talk. Concentrating.

660
00:35:49,875 --> 00:35:51,916
Rodrick, what are you doing?

661
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:53,583
Isn't one game enough?

662
00:35:55,125 --> 00:35:57,375
You think I'm here
to play games?

663
00:35:58,208 --> 00:36:00,833
Are those Mom Bucks?

664
00:36:00,916 --> 00:36:02,958
Millions of dollars worth.

665
00:36:03,041 --> 00:36:04,041
[sniffs]

666
00:36:05,916 --> 00:36:08,250
That's amazing. Wow!

667
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:11,375
So, this is why you wanted
to come to Leisure Towers.

668
00:36:11,458 --> 00:36:14,291
Bingo. Now you're
starting to get it.

669
00:36:14,375 --> 00:36:15,916
Come on. Let's split it up.

670
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:18,875
- Ah! Da, da, da, da! Not so fast.
- [grunts]

671
00:36:18,958 --> 00:36:20,250
Go find your own supply.

672
00:36:20,333 --> 00:36:22,833
Come on, Rodrick. You owe me.

673
00:36:23,750 --> 00:36:28,250
[groans] Fine, here's a hundred.
Don't spend it all in one place.

674
00:36:29,125 --> 00:36:32,583
Now, why don't you go change?
You look like you wet yourself.

675
00:36:32,666 --> 00:36:34,833
I can't. Grandpa's
in the bathroom.

676
00:36:34,916 --> 00:36:36,916
Then use the one in the lobby.

677
00:36:37,750 --> 00:36:40,392
[Greg narrating] <i>I've gotta hand it
to Rodrick on this Mom Bucks thing.</i>

678
00:36:40,416 --> 00:36:42,500
<i>Every time I think I've
figured him all out,</i>

679
00:36:42,583 --> 00:36:44,125
<i>he surprises me
with something new.</i>

680
00:36:44,916 --> 00:36:47,625
It's pea soup again
tonight, I hear.

681
00:36:47,708 --> 00:36:50,083
That sounds pretty good to me.

682
00:36:50,875 --> 00:36:52,416
[shoes squeaking]

683
00:36:52,500 --> 00:36:53,625
Huh?

684
00:36:53,708 --> 00:36:54,916
[both gasp]

685
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:58,333
[elderly person] Oh, my.

686
00:36:58,416 --> 00:36:59,458
[groans]

687
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:01,583
[chuckles]

688
00:37:06,541 --> 00:37:07,583
[grunting]

689
00:37:09,458 --> 00:37:11,750
[elderly person] Hi, Merle!
Going to bingo tonight?

690
00:37:11,833 --> 00:37:13,583
[Merle] I wouldn't
miss it for the world.

691
00:37:13,666 --> 00:37:16,708
[elderly person] Well, you can
kiss your winning streak goodbye.

692
00:37:16,791 --> 00:37:18,958
I'm bringing a good
luck charm with me.

693
00:37:19,041 --> 00:37:21,541
- [squeaks]
- Oh! Isn't he cute?

694
00:37:21,625 --> 00:37:25,291
Merle, Irene, bingo tonight?

695
00:37:25,375 --> 00:37:26,708
Ha! We'll see.

696
00:37:26,791 --> 00:37:32,500
Can you believe my luck last
week? Two games in a row.

697
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:36,833
It was all thanks
to my lucky charm.

698
00:37:36,916 --> 00:37:38,083
[squeaks]

699
00:37:38,166 --> 00:37:39,916
[whimpers]

700
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,208
[flushes]

701
00:37:41,291 --> 00:37:42,375
[shouts]

702
00:37:48,333 --> 00:37:50,083
Say…

703
00:37:50,166 --> 00:37:52,208
"Boys size small?"

704
00:37:52,291 --> 00:37:54,375
[gasps] A Peeping Tom!

705
00:37:54,458 --> 00:37:55,458
[shouts]

706
00:37:58,583 --> 00:38:02,083
We see you in there,
Boy Size Small!

707
00:38:02,166 --> 00:38:05,000
[Irene] We're gonna hand
you over to the authorities!

708
00:38:05,083 --> 00:38:07,208
[Merle] They'll put
you in the slammer!

709
00:38:10,750 --> 00:38:13,208
- [Irene] Where did he go?
- [elderly person] I don't see him.

710
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:14,708
[Irene] Did he give us the slip?

711
00:38:14,791 --> 00:38:15,666
[squeaks]

712
00:38:15,750 --> 00:38:16,875
[shouts]

713
00:38:16,958 --> 00:38:18,125
- [screams]
- There he is!

714
00:38:18,208 --> 00:38:20,291
He's on the move, ladies!

715
00:38:21,875 --> 00:38:25,166
[laughing]

716
00:38:26,708 --> 00:38:27,875
[grunts]

717
00:38:27,958 --> 00:38:30,083
[shouting]

718
00:38:30,166 --> 00:38:31,250
After him!

719
00:38:31,750 --> 00:38:32,625
[alarm sounds]

720
00:38:32,708 --> 00:38:34,916
- Huh? Huh?
- [grunts]

721
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:37,375
- We're coming through!
- Hey! Watch it!

722
00:38:37,458 --> 00:38:39,541
- Don't let him get away!
- [panting]

723
00:38:42,291 --> 00:38:43,666
[ladies muttering]

724
00:38:43,750 --> 00:38:45,166
[sighs]

725
00:38:45,250 --> 00:38:47,208
- [yelps]
- You get out of here!

726
00:38:47,291 --> 00:38:48,291
- [shouts]
- [chattering]

727
00:38:48,375 --> 00:38:50,000
[elderly person]
Killing my bingo buzz!

728
00:38:50,083 --> 00:38:51,750
[Irene] There he is!

729
00:38:51,833 --> 00:38:53,416
There's Boy Size Small.

730
00:38:56,166 --> 00:38:59,041
- Come back here! We're gonna get you!
- Yeah! Yeah!

731
00:39:00,583 --> 00:39:01,583
There he is! Come on!

732
00:39:01,666 --> 00:39:02,958
- [shouts]
- [guard] Hey, kid!

733
00:39:03,041 --> 00:39:05,000
- Come back here!
- Come on. Wait!

734
00:39:05,083 --> 00:39:06,309
- Out of my way!
- Hey! Get off!

735
00:39:06,333 --> 00:39:07,750
Where do you think you're going?

736
00:39:08,583 --> 00:39:09,583
[panting]

737
00:39:09,666 --> 00:39:10,666
[gasps]

738
00:39:11,166 --> 00:39:13,458
Hmm, what do we have here?

739
00:39:14,583 --> 00:39:16,375
- Oh!
- Uh…

740
00:39:18,791 --> 00:39:19,791
That's nasty.

