went straight to Mommy and Daddy.

946
00:51:20,083 --> 00:51:21,791
You ratted me out!

947
00:51:21,875 --> 00:51:25,458
No snitching. That's
Rodrick Rule number one!

948
00:51:25,541 --> 00:51:29,041
I thought rule number
one was no apostrophes.

949
00:51:29,875 --> 00:51:31,750
And besides, that's
not what happened!

950
00:51:31,833 --> 00:51:35,750
I took you under my
wing! I trusted you!

951
00:51:38,750 --> 00:51:42,833
Yeah, it's been great.
You've taught me a lot.

952
00:51:43,875 --> 00:51:47,750
Yeah, and the only reason that I
did was because you had dirt on me.

953
00:51:47,833 --> 00:51:50,750
And now you don't.
So, watch your back.

954
00:51:51,916 --> 00:51:53,291
But...

955
00:51:53,375 --> 00:51:56,750
I thought you were
cool. Guess I was wrong.

956
00:52:06,958 --> 00:52:11,500
Introducing the Amazing
Rowley Jefferson!

957
00:52:12,541 --> 00:52:14,541
Whoo, yeah!

958
00:52:15,291 --> 00:52:21,375
And with a wave of my magic
wand, the egg has disappeared!

959
00:52:21,458 --> 00:52:22,458
[egg breaks]

960
00:52:23,791 --> 00:52:28,208
Greg, you were supposed to turn the cup
upside down before you gave it back to me.

961
00:52:29,625 --> 00:52:32,041
Huh? Oh, yeah. Next time.

962
00:52:32,125 --> 00:52:36,583
If we don't get this right by
Friday night, we're never gonna win!

963
00:52:36,666 --> 00:52:40,375
We're not gonna win, Rowley. We're
competing against high schoolers.

964
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:45,083
Well, at least we don't have to
go against your brother's band.

965
00:52:45,583 --> 00:52:49,166
[sighs] Yes, we do. They
got a replacement drummer.

966
00:52:49,250 --> 00:52:50,625
Oh.

967
00:52:51,250 --> 00:52:53,041
Hey, I've got an idea.

968
00:52:53,625 --> 00:52:55,875
I was thinking maybe I
could be the magician

969
00:52:55,958 --> 00:52:58,291
and you could be the assistant.

970
00:52:58,375 --> 00:53:00,250
It's way more
believable that way.

971
00:53:00,333 --> 00:53:04,250
But it's my magic set! I
got it for my birthday!

972
00:53:05,416 --> 00:53:07,291
Okay, okay.

973
00:53:07,375 --> 00:53:08,500
- Gee whiz.
- [door opens]

974
00:53:08,583 --> 00:53:10,375
Hey, guys!

975
00:53:10,458 --> 00:53:13,708
Hi, Rodrick. Wanna
see some magic?

976
00:53:13,791 --> 00:53:17,083
Nah, wouldn't want you to spoil it
for me. Save it for the big night.

977
00:53:17,166 --> 00:53:19,125
Oh. Okay!

978
00:53:19,208 --> 00:53:21,083
Wait. What are
you doing up here?

979
00:53:21,166 --> 00:53:25,416
I found something on the kitchen
table. Thought it might belong to you.

980
00:53:26,583 --> 00:53:28,291
Hey! Give it back!

981
00:53:28,375 --> 00:53:33,291
Easy there, little brother. I
was just returning your property.

982
00:53:34,416 --> 00:53:37,291
Wait. You didn't
read it, did you?

983
00:53:37,375 --> 00:53:40,666
Read it? [scoffs] Way
too many words for me.

984
00:53:41,375 --> 00:53:42,375
[sighs]

985
00:53:43,458 --> 00:53:46,625
I did look at the
pictures though.

986
00:53:46,708 --> 00:53:48,708
And boy, I learned a lot.

987
00:53:48,791 --> 00:53:53,250
Like what really happened
at Leisure Towers.

988
00:53:54,791 --> 00:53:55,791
That's private.

989
00:53:55,875 --> 00:53:58,500
Well, it's about to be public.

990
00:53:58,583 --> 00:54:00,250
See, I know people.

991
00:54:00,333 --> 00:54:03,916
And those people have little brothers
and sisters that go to your school.

992
00:54:04,000 --> 00:54:07,125
And I'll bet they're gonna love
reading about your little adventure

993
00:54:07,208 --> 00:54:08,208
in the women's bathroom.

994
00:54:08,291 --> 00:54:09,625
You wouldn't!

995
00:54:09,708 --> 00:54:13,500
You ratted me out. These
are the consequences.

996
00:54:14,083 --> 00:54:15,500
- [shouts, grunts]
- [grunts]

997
00:54:15,583 --> 00:54:16,583
Give me that!

998
00:54:22,583 --> 00:54:23,750
Oh! [chuckles]

999
00:54:23,833 --> 00:54:25,250
- [Greg grunts]
- [Rodrick] Ow!

1000
00:54:27,500 --> 00:54:28,666
No!

1001
00:54:29,791 --> 00:54:30,958
Ooh!

1002
00:54:33,541 --> 00:54:34,666
Nice catch.

1003
00:54:34,750 --> 00:54:35,750
[chuckles]

1004
00:54:36,250 --> 00:54:37,583
- Oops!
- [phone beeps]

1005
00:54:38,208 --> 00:54:41,041
[phone chiming]

1006
00:54:41,125 --> 00:54:42,875
No!

1007
00:54:44,958 --> 00:54:45,958
My bad.

1008
00:54:47,333 --> 00:54:50,541
[Greg narrating] <i>Believe me, I did
not want to go to school the next day.</i>

1009
00:54:50,625 --> 00:54:55,041
<i>After Rodrick's little text was sent
out, my reputation was gonna be ruined.</i>

1010
00:54:56,375 --> 00:54:58,166
<i>But I knew I couldn't
hide forever.</i>

1011
00:54:58,250 --> 00:55:01,916
<i>So, I just decided to bite the
bullet and get it over with.</i>

1012
00:55:02,875 --> 00:55:04,875
[students chattering]

1013
00:55:08,125 --> 00:55:10,750
All right, Rowley.
Let's do this.

1014
00:55:11,291 --> 00:55:12,291
Rowley?

1015
00:55:13,583 --> 00:55:15,625
You got this, Greg! [chuckles]

1016
00:55:15,708 --> 00:55:16,833
[sighs]

1017
00:55:19,666 --> 00:55:22,041
- This week's flying by, like, so fast.
- I know!

1018
00:55:22,125 --> 00:55:24,041
- Wait. Wait. Is that Greg Heffley?
- Look!

1019
00:55:24,583 --> 00:55:25,833
[both] Whoa!

1020
00:55:27,625 --> 00:55:28,625
[cheering]

1021
00:55:28,708 --> 00:55:29,791
What?

1022
00:55:31,958 --> 00:55:35,916
[chanting] Greg! Greg! Greg! Greg!
Greg! Greg! Greg! Greg! Greg! Greg!

1023
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:38,958
[Greg narrating] <i>It took me a few
minutes to figure out what was going on.</i>

1024
00:55:40,000 --> 00:55:42,583
<i>Rodrick's message went
out to all of his friends.</i>

1025
00:55:43,166 --> 00:55:44,166
[phone beeps]

1026
00:55:44,250 --> 00:55:47,083
<i>His friends told their brothers
and sisters what happened to me,</i>

1027
00:55:47,166 --> 00:55:48,458
<i>and they told their friends.</i>

1028
00:55:48,541 --> 00:55:49,601
<i>Just like Rodrick planned it.</i>

1029
00:55:49,625 --> 00:55:51,583
<i>But I guess people
mixed up the facts</i>

1030
00:55:51,666 --> 00:55:55,541
<i>because by the time I got to school,
the story was totally scrambled.</i>

1031
00:55:58,250 --> 00:55:59,500
<i>Somehow the story went</i>

1032
00:55:59,583 --> 00:56:02,791
<i>from me being caught in the
ladies' room at Leisure Towers,</i>

1033
00:56:02,875 --> 00:56:07,166
<i>to me sneaking into a bingo game and
walking off with the grand prize.</i>

1034
00:56:07,250 --> 00:56:09,750
Bingo! [chuckles]

1035
00:56:09,833 --> 00:56:10,833
- [grunts]
- [grunts]

1036
00:56:10,916 --> 00:56:14,458
<i>And the only thing people got right was
me getting chased by the security guards.</i>

1037
00:56:14,541 --> 00:56:16,916
<i>But even that stuff
got exaggerated.</i>

1038
00:56:18,833 --> 00:56:19,958
- [growls]
- Hey!

1039
00:56:20,041 --> 00:56:21,041
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

1040
00:56:21,125 --> 00:56:23,083
[blows raspberry]

1041
00:56:27,416 --> 00:56:29,434
[Greg narrating] <i>Even the
thing with the vending machines</i>

1042
00:56:29,458 --> 00:56:30,541
<i>made it into the story,</i>

1043
00:56:30,625 --> 00:56:32,291
<i>but the facts got
mixed up there too.</i>

1044
00:56:33,833 --> 00:56:36,833
<i>I wasn't exactly in a hurry to
set the record straight, though.</i>

1045
00:56:36,916 --> 00:56:40,250
<i>Because the new version of the
story made me look pretty sick.</i>

1046
00:56:42,250 --> 00:56:43,875
[crowd cheering]

1047
00:56:44,500 --> 00:56:46,666
<i>So Rodrick's plan backfired,</i>

1048
00:56:46,750 --> 00:56:49,059
<i>and I got a taste of what it's
like to be popular for once.</i>

1049
00:56:49,083 --> 00:56:51,541
Wow! This is so cool!
I got his autograph!

1050
00:56:52,375 --> 00:56:54,135
[Greg narrating] <i>But I
knew it wouldn't last.</i>

1051
00:56:54,791 --> 00:56:58,208
<i>Because the second I took the stage as
Rowley's assistant at the talent show,</i>

1052
00:56:58,291 --> 00:57:00,250
<i>my reputation was
gonna take a nosedive.</i>

1053
00:57:00,333 --> 00:57:03,875
[sighs] I don't get why I
have to go to this thing.

1054
00:57:03,958 --> 00:57:08,500
You're here to cheer on your
brother, Rodrick, and your bandmates.

1055
00:57:08,583 --> 00:57:10,166
Ex-bandmates.

1056
00:57:10,875 --> 00:57:14,916
[grunts] D-Does the rec
center have a bathroom?

1057
00:57:18,291 --> 00:57:21,041
[engine revs]

1058
00:57:24,958 --> 00:57:27,875
[chattering]

1059
00:57:27,958 --> 00:57:31,208
[Frank] Okay. Everyone, hop
out. I'll go look for a spot.

1060
00:57:40,166 --> 00:57:42,500
Yo! What's shaking, little man?

1061
00:57:42,583 --> 00:57:43,791
Uh, nothing much.

1062
00:57:43,875 --> 00:57:47,541
So, we heard about your little
dustup over at Leisure Towers.

1063
00:57:47,625 --> 00:57:48,625
The what?

1064
00:57:49,250 --> 00:57:50,375
Oh, yeah. That.

1065
00:57:50,458 --> 00:57:53,041
Dude, you're a legend!

1066
00:57:53,125 --> 00:57:55,500
An absolute lege, dude!

1067
00:57:55,583 --> 00:57:56,875
Yeah, I guess.

1068
00:57:56,958 --> 00:57:58,625
So, we were thinking,

1069
00:57:59,333 --> 00:58:03,666
if we join forces tonight,
we could win this thing.

1070
00:58:03,750 --> 00:58:05,458
Huh? I-I don't get it.

1071
00:58:05,541 --> 00:58:08,750
You've got the middle school vote.
And we've got the high school vote.

1072
00:58:08,833 --> 00:58:11,208
And I've got the Mom
vote. Not to brag.

1073
00:58:11,291 --> 00:58:13,125
What do you mean "join forces"?

1074
00:58:13,208 --> 00:58:18,250
How'd you like to be
Löded Diper's new drummer?

1075
00:58:18,791 --> 00:58:20,833
What? I don't know
how to play the drums.

1076
00:58:20,916 --> 00:58:22,875
We know your brother's
been teaching you.

1077
00:58:22,958 --> 00:58:26,583
Time for the student
to become the master.

1078
00:58:26,666 --> 00:58:31,291
Sorry, guys. I'm in my friend's
magic act. I can't get out of it.

1079
00:58:31,375 --> 00:58:37,708
That's where Larry comes in. We'll
do a clean swap. You for him.

1080
00:58:37,791 --> 00:58:39,791
Magic is my real passion.

1081
00:58:40,333 --> 00:58:41,666
Ta-da!

1082
00:58:42,166 --> 00:58:46,166
I just can't do that to
Rodrick. He's my brother.

1083
00:58:47,250 --> 00:58:48,833
Why don't you just
think it over?

1084
00:58:49,750 --> 00:58:52,416
Maybe this is your
turn to shine, my dude.

1085
00:59:04,083 --> 00:59:05,541
I'll think about it.

1086
00:59:06,041 --> 00:59:08,750
That's all we're
asking, little man.

1087
00:59:13,208 --> 00:59:16,208
[audience chattering]

1088
00:59:16,833 --> 00:59:18,250
[mike feedback]

1089
00:59:34,333 --> 00:59:36,416
- Yo! It's Greg!
- That's Greg Heffley!

1090
00:59:37,041 --> 00:59:39,875
- You're a legend, dude.
- [chuckles] Yeah, thanks.

1091
00:59:41,166 --> 00:59:42,458
Oh!

1092
00:59:42,541 --> 00:59:44,916
Is that Boy Size Small?

1093
00:59:47,958 --> 00:59:49,000
Where were you?

1094
00:59:49,083 --> 00:59:50,500
I just got held up.

1095
00:59:59,708 --> 01:00:01,541
[orchestral music playing]

1096
01:00:01,625 --> 01:00:04,666
Oh, this is so exciting.

1097
01:00:06,166 --> 01:00:09,750
[announcer] <i>Ladies and
gentlemen, boys and girls!</i>

1098
01:00:09,833 --> 01:00:14,458
- <i>Welcome to the Talent Show!</i>
- [cheering]

1099
01:00:18,750 --> 01:00:21,333
[playing off-key]

1100
01:00:21,833 --> 01:00:23,500
[crowd murmuring]

1101
01:00:25,500 --> 01:00:27,750
[groans]

1102
01:00:38,000 --> 01:00:42,750
Then the man in the orthopedic
shoes said, "I stand corrected!"

1103
01:00:42,833 --> 01:00:45,000
- [laughs]
- [grunts]

1104
01:00:45,083 --> 01:00:47,000
[house music playing]

1105
01:00:49,333 --> 01:00:51,208
[beatboxing]

1106
01:00:51,291 --> 01:00:53,208
[beatboxing]

1107
01:00:53,291 --> 01:00:54,291
Oh.

1108
01:00:54,375 --> 01:00:58,666
♪ <i>Amor fatal</i> ♪

1109
01:00:58,750 --> 01:01:01,500
♪ <i>Tremendo</i> ♪

1110
01:01:01,583 --> 01:01:05,375
♪ <i>Tremendo</i> ♪

1111
01:01:11,250 --> 01:01:12,517
[whispering] I've
got to get ready.

1112
01:01:12,541 --> 01:01:14,500
- Break a leg, Greg.
- Okay.

1113
01:01:14,583 --> 01:01:17,625
Do your best for Rowley. Try
and look like you're having fun.

1114
01:01:17,708 --> 01:01:18,708
Hey, Greg.

1115
01:01:19,625 --> 01:01:24,125
Can't wait to see you do your
magic. [scoffs] So uncool.

1116
01:01:30,208 --> 01:01:32,541
Are you ready for
some magic, Manny?

1117
01:01:32,625 --> 01:01:35,208
- Yay!
- Yes, you are. Yes, you are.

1118
01:01:35,291 --> 01:01:38,291
[Bill] Ladies and
gentlemen, boys and girls.

1119
01:01:38,791 --> 01:01:41,833
We have just one
question for you.

1120
01:01:41,916 --> 01:01:43,583
- [snores, gasps]
- Wake up!

1121
01:01:43,666 --> 01:01:48,250
Are you ready to rock?

1122
01:01:48,333 --> 01:01:49,333
[mike feedback]

1123
01:01:49,416 --> 01:01:51,083
Yeah!

1124
01:01:51,166 --> 01:01:57,000
Now, before we explode your eardrums
with a blast of pure rock and roll,

1125
01:01:58,041 --> 01:02:03,000
it's time to introduce the
newest member of Löded Diper.

1126
01:02:03,500 --> 01:02:09,666
Please join me in welcoming
Greg Heffley to the stage!

1127
01:02:09,750 --> 01:02:10,750
- [gasps]
- Greg?

1128
01:02:13,250 --> 01:02:14,916
[cheering]

1129
01:02:20,125 --> 01:02:22,916
Come on, little dude.
Give 'em a taste.

1130
01:02:25,791 --> 01:02:27,833
Oh. Oof.

1131
01:02:27,916 --> 01:02:29,236
- [audience chattering]
- [laughs]

1132
01:02:43,166 --> 01:02:44,333
[cheering]

1133
01:02:44,416 --> 01:02:46,541
Yeah, right on.

1134
01:02:46,625 --> 01:02:48,375
We love you, Greg!

1135
01:02:48,458 --> 01:02:54,125
[chanting] Greg! Greg! Greg! Greg!
Greg! Greg! Greg! Greg! Greg! Greg!

1136
01:03:15,541 --> 01:03:18,375
Yo, you ready to blow
the roof off this place?

1137
01:03:38,333 --> 01:03:40,375
Hey. You're missing the show.

1138
01:03:40,958 --> 01:03:45,083
What are you doing out here?
Aren't you supposed to be on stage?

1139
01:03:45,166 --> 01:03:47,333
I don't know. It
didn't feel right.

1140
01:03:47,416 --> 01:03:50,291
Well, maybe that's
because it's not right.

1141
01:03:50,833 --> 01:03:55,250
You stole my spot just to get
back at me for the diary thing.

1142
01:03:55,333 --> 01:03:59,458
Pretty much. But it
wasn't just about payback.

1143
01:03:59,541 --> 01:04:01,500
[scoffs] Yeah, right.

1144
01:04:02,208 --> 01:04:05,208
I, uh, wanted you
to be proud of me.

1145
01:04:05,291 --> 01:04:07,916
Proud of you? For what?

1146
01:04:08,541 --> 01:04:11,291
I-I know. I-It was dumb.

1147
01:04:13,166 --> 01:04:16,000
I've got something that I've got
to get off my chest too, I guess.

1148
01:04:16,083 --> 01:04:20,291
I... I shouldn't have
taken your diary.

1149
01:04:21,125 --> 01:04:24,125
That wasn't… cool.

1150
01:04:26,250 --> 01:04:30,333
I don't understand why we can't
just get along like normal brothers.

1151
01:04:30,833 --> 01:04:33,708
This is normal. Brothers fight.

1152
01:04:34,208 --> 01:04:37,375
We just… took it too far.

1153
01:04:37,875 --> 01:04:42,500
But do you think we're gonna be
all right, like, in the long run?

1154
01:04:42,583 --> 01:04:45,375
What? What do you mean?

1155
01:04:45,458 --> 01:04:49,583
Well, Dad and his brothers don't even
see each other on holidays anymore.

1156
01:04:49,666 --> 01:04:51,875
Is that gonna happen to us?

1157
01:04:57,416 --> 01:05:01,500
Heck, yeah, we're gonna see each
other on the holidays. We're family.

1158
01:05:04,916 --> 01:05:07,625
But I am not hosting.
Too much work.

1159
01:05:07,708 --> 01:05:09,750
Okay. Deal.

1160
01:05:09,833 --> 01:05:12,750
Listen, me and you are
gonna have our battles.

1161
01:05:13,333 --> 01:05:15,875
But I really hope you know
that when the chips are down,

1162
01:05:15,958 --> 01:05:18,666
and I mean really down,

1163
01:05:18,750 --> 01:05:22,041
I'm gonna have your back.
And you better have mine.

1164
01:05:22,125 --> 01:05:24,875
Because it's the Heffley
brothers against the world.

1165
01:05:26,458 --> 01:05:27,625
The Heffley brothers.

1166
01:05:29,833 --> 01:05:32,875
[crowd cheering]
Greg! Greg! Greg!

1167
01:05:33,500 --> 01:05:37,041
So? Are you gonna keep sitting out
here, or are you gonna go make me proud?

1168
01:05:37,625 --> 01:05:41,541
Yeah, about that. These
don't belong to me.

1169
01:05:47,083 --> 01:05:50,416
Like you said, there's only
one Rodrick. And that's you.

1170
01:05:52,583 --> 01:05:53,750
[shouts, grunts]

1171
01:05:53,833 --> 01:05:55,291
[laughing]

1172
01:05:55,375 --> 01:05:57,291
[Rodrick] Wait a second.
I'm still grounded.

1173
01:05:57,375 --> 01:05:59,416
[Greg] Oh, yeah. I
forgot about that.

1174
01:05:59,500 --> 01:06:04,291
[Rodrick] Oh, well. Rodrick Rule number
ten. Always go out in a blaze of glory.

1175
01:06:04,375 --> 01:06:06,500
[both laugh]

1176
01:06:06,583 --> 01:06:08,559
- [crowd jeering]
- [crowd member] Come on, entertain us!

1177
01:06:08,583 --> 01:06:13,000
Stand by. Uh, we're just having
some, uh, technical difficulties.

1178
01:06:13,083 --> 01:06:14,541
[drums beating]

1179
01:06:14,625 --> 01:06:16,708
All right!

1180
01:06:16,791 --> 01:06:22,541
Please welcome Löded
Diper's original drummer,

1181
01:06:22,625 --> 01:06:24,583
Rodrick Heffley!

1182
01:06:24,666 --> 01:06:26,833
- Whoo!
- [crowd cheering]

1183
01:06:26,916 --> 01:06:28,166
- What?
- Rodrick?

1184
01:06:38,083 --> 01:06:40,041
Rodrick rules!

1185
01:06:40,125 --> 01:06:42,250
We love you, Rodrick!

1186
01:06:43,125 --> 01:06:44,583
Unbelievable.

1187
01:06:47,791 --> 01:06:51,750
Greg, you do understand
that you're both grounded?

1188
01:06:52,250 --> 01:06:53,291
Yeah, I know.

1189
01:06:53,375 --> 01:06:55,583
Rodrick isn't supposed
to be up there.

1190
01:06:56,333 --> 01:06:59,583
So, we have no choice but
to extend your punishment.

1191
01:07:01,791 --> 01:07:02,791
It's worth it.

1192
01:07:02,875 --> 01:07:05,416
He's my brother.
I've got his back.

1193
01:07:09,583 --> 01:07:12,583
You're raising some
good boys there, Son.

1194
01:07:13,708 --> 01:07:14,708
Yeah.

1195
01:07:19,791 --> 01:07:21,708
[drumsticks hitting]

1196
01:07:30,625 --> 01:07:32,083
♪ <i>All right!</i> ♪

1197
01:07:34,833 --> 01:07:36,708
- ♪ <i>Oh, yeah!</i> ♪
- [chuckles] Yippee!

1198
01:07:36,791 --> 01:07:38,666
- Whoo!
- Whoo-hoo!

1199
01:07:39,166 --> 01:07:40,291
[grunts]

1200
01:07:41,250 --> 01:07:42,250
♪ <i>Yeah!</i> ♪

1201
01:07:43,708 --> 01:07:48,541
♪ <i>You never liked us So
you sent us underground</i> ♪

1202
01:07:48,625 --> 01:07:50,125
[grunts]

1203
01:07:50,208 --> 01:07:51,208
Come on!

1204
01:07:51,291 --> 01:07:56,500
♪ <i>You never listened So
we turned up the sound</i> ♪

1205
01:07:57,000 --> 01:07:58,458
Huh?

1206
01:07:59,333 --> 01:08:04,208
♪ <i>And now you're quaking
As I'm standing on stage</i> ♪

1207
01:08:04,291 --> 01:08:06,791
- Yeah! Löded Diper!
- [Bill] Uh-huh! Yeah!

1208
01:08:06,875 --> 01:08:10,625
♪ <i>That's why you're shaking
'Cause you're feeling your age</i> ♪

1209
01:08:10,708 --> 01:08:12,541
Whoo! That's my jam!

1210
01:08:14,291 --> 01:08:18,208
♪ <i>Your arms are waving
As you get on your feet</i> ♪

1211
01:08:18,291 --> 01:08:21,666
♪ <i>Your booty swaying Like
you ate some bad meat</i> ♪

1212
01:08:21,750 --> 01:08:26,083
♪ <i>So we say Can
you smell us now?</i> ♪

1213
01:08:26,166 --> 01:08:29,583
♪ <i>Filling up your nostrils
And you're mopping your brow</i> ♪

1214
01:08:29,666 --> 01:08:31,750
♪ <i>Come on Can you smell us…</i> ♪

